          "type": "user",
          "text": "<task-notification>\n<task-id>a00a********3797</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>tool********HY3D</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-reme/72662479-e828-4629-84b4-9cf50ce6d019/tasks/a00ad01904abf3797.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Simplify branch changes\" completed</summary>\n<result>Here is my review, Leo.\n\n---\n\n## Simplification Findings\n\n### 1. `main.rs:239-244` -- Redundant `AdvertisementSpec` construction\n\nThe node constructs `AdvertisementSpec` field-by-field, hardcoding `service_type: \"_reme._tcp.local.\".to_owned()`. There is already `AdvertisementSpec::new(port, routing_key)` which sets `service_type` to `DEFAULT_SERVICE_TYPE` and `txt_records` to an empty map. The client at `apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs:215-218` already uses this constructor with struct update syntax.\n\nThe node version could use:\n\n```rust\nlet spec = AdvertisementSpec {\n    txt_records: txt,\n    ..AdvertisementSpec::new(port, routing_key)\n};\n```\n\nThis eliminates the hardcoded service type string and is consistent with how the client does it.\n\n### 2. `main.rs:246-248` -- Fully qualified trait method call is unnecessary\n\nThe code calls `reme_discovery::DiscoveryBackend::start_advertising(backend.as_ref(), spec)` and `reme_discovery::DiscoveryBackend::stop_advertising(backend.as_ref())` using fully qualified syntax. Since `MdnsSdBackend` is the concrete type and `DiscoveryBackend` is already in scope via the `use` at line 72, regular method calls `backend.start_advertising(spec).await` and `backend.stop_advertising().await` work fine -- exactly how the client calls them at `apps/client/src/discovery/mod.rs:220` and how the tests call them.\n\nThis would also let you drop the `DiscoveryBackend` import or use it more idiomatically.\n\n### 3. `main.rs:262-269` -- `stop_mdns_advertising` helper barely earns its keep\n\nThe function body is:\n\n```rust\nasync fn stop_mdns_advertising(backend: 