(line 258–261):** The justification (\"body is trivially simple\") is accurate — the function is a 4-line if-let with one call. The annotation is almost certainly a false positive from the Clippy version in use; suppressing it here is correct. This suppression is fully justified.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe implementation is functionally correct for the happy path. The material issue is the missing `shutdown()` call — the mDNS daemon's background thread is leaked and goodbye packets may not be sent reliably. The unused-clone issue is a code smell. The `unwrap_or(false)` vs `unwrap_or(defaults...)` inconsistency is a latent bug if the default changes. All three are worth fixing before merge.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>54634</total_tokens><tool_uses>18</tool_uses><duration_ms>96728</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>",
